%20to%20receive%20emails%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Education%20notifying%20them%20that%20they've%20met%20the%20payment%20threshold%20and%20qualify%20for%20debt%20cancellation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20emails%2C%20multiple%20of%20which%20were%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20had%20the%20subject%20line%3A%20%26quot%3BYou're%20eligible%20to%20have%20your%20student%20loan(s)%20discharged.%26quot%3B%20It%20said%20that%20the%20department%20is%20working%20with%20the%20borrower's%20servicer%20to%20process%20the%20relief%20%26quot%3Bover%20the%20next%20several%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20department%20will%20send%20the%20borrower's%20discharge%20information%20to%20the%20servicer%20after%20October%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncome-based%20repayment%20plans%20give%20borrowers%20monthly%20payments%20intended%20to%20be%20affordable%20based%20on%20income%2C%20with%20the%20promise%20of%20loan%20forgiveness%20after%2020%20or%2025%20years.%20As%20of%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%202025%2C%202%20million%20borrowers%20were%20enrolled%20in%20IBR%2C%20per%20Federal%20Student%20Aid%20data.%20The%20department%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-paused-ibr-trump-halts-borrower-debt-relief-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epaused%20relief%20through%20IBR%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20July%2C%20saying%20in%20a%20Federal%20Student%20Aid%20notice%20that%20the%20department%20needed%20time%20to%20ensure%20payment%20counts%20are%20accurate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20loan%20servicer%20will%20notify%20you%20if%20and%20when%20your%20IBR%20discharge%20has%20been%20processed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20email%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20may%20take%20some%20time%20for%20your%20loan%20servicer%20to%20process%20your%20discharge%20and%20for%20your%20account%20to%20reflect%20this%20change.%20Most%20borrowers%20will%20have%20their%20discharge%20processed%20within%20two%20weeks%2C%20but%20for%20some%20borrowers%2C%20processing%20could%20take%20more%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorrowers%20who%20want%20to%20opt%20out%20of%20the%20IBR%20relief%20must%20do%20so%20by%20October%2021%20by%20contacting%20their%20loan%20servicer%20and%20saying%20that%20they%20are%20not%20interested%20in%20the%20relief.%20The%20department%20said%20in%20its%20email%20that%20a%20reason%20to%20opt%20out%20might%20be%20to%20avoid%20a%20state%20tax%20liability%2C%20but%20noted%20that%20those%20who%20do%20opt%20out%20are%20required%20to%20continue%20making%20payments%20on%20their%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20increased%20urgency%20for%20loan%20forgiveness%20to%20be%20processed%20before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20A%202021%20provision%20in%20the%20American%20Rescue%20Plan%20that%20made%20forgiveness%20tax-free%20is%20expiring%2C%20meaning%20borrowers%20who%20receive%20debt%20relief%20could%20be%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20tax%20bills%20after%20January%201%2C%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Federation%20of%20Teachers%2C%20which%20has%20members%20enrolled%20in%20IBR%20plans%20and%20Public%20Service%20Loan%20Forgiveness%2C%20filed%20a%20complaint%20in%20September%20urging%20the%20department%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-delays-pslf-debt-relief-taxes-education-department-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecancel%20the%20loans%20of%20borrowers%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20have%20met%20their%20payment%20thresholds%20before%20the%20relief%20is%20once%20again%20taxable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20IBR%20processing%20is%20resuming%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20is%20still%20working%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-student-loan-debt-repayment-overhaul-borrowing-caps-professional-degrees-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elimit%20future%20forgiveness%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmajor-student-loan-debt-repayment-changes-trump-kicks-off-negotiations-